  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/industry/\" rel=\"tag\">产业新闻</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/12/03/toshiba-to-buy-ocz-assets-for-35-million/\"><img alt=\"OCZ Vector 150 SSD\" src=\"http://hss-prod.hss.aol.com/hss/storage/adam/3fd0e986c5f0b0806e6dfe01f73601b9/ocz-vector-150-ssd.jpg\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n果不其然，OCZ <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/11/27/ocz-declares-bankruptcy/\">面临破产</a>后，最终来接手的正是传了好久绯闻的东芝。今天后者在破产拍卖中以 3,500 万美元的价格成功接盘，预计在明年 1 月的时候就可将前者的 SSD 业务收入囊中。以 <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/tag/ocz\">OCZ</a> 的角度来看，这笔交易所带来的资金可以帮助他们在过渡期内完成客户的订单。而东芝这边，在有了 OCZ 的控制器芯片和闪存技术后，其未来的 SSD 产品应该会有不少值得期待的地方。最终以这样的方式退出，对 OCZ 来说应该是抱有遗憾的，但没办法，优胜劣汰本就是市场之常态啊。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2013/12/03/toshiba-to-buy-ocz-assets-for-35-million/\">Engadget</a>、<span class=\"via\"><a href=\"http://www.pcworld.com/article/2068522/toshiba-buys-oczs-belly-up-ssd-business-where-does-that-leave-your-warranty-.html#tk.twt_pcworld\" target=\"_blank\">PCWorld</a></span><br />\n引用来源：<span class=\"source\"><a href=\"http://ir.ocz.com/news/detail/3014/ocz-reaches-agreement-with-toshiba-corporation-to-acquire-solid-state-drive-business\" target=\"_blank\">OCZ</a></span>、<span class=\"source\"><a href=\"http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20131202006437/en/Toshiba-Corporation-Purchase-Assets-OCZ\" target=\"_blank\">BusinessWire</a></span></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/12/03/toshiba-to-buy-ocz-assets-for-35-million/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20780788/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/12/03/toshiba-to-buy-ocz-assets-for-35-million/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on th